|fp|t-title|at|A bit of History |fp||at|
Precision was invented by a Chinese businessman called CC Wei in the late 1960's.  It quickly gained an international reputation following its introduction onto the world stage by the Chinese National Team and was soon after adopted by the famous Italian Blue Team.  

Two members of the Blue Team (Giorgio Belladonna and Benito Garozzo) later wrote the first description of 'Super-Precision', which employed a number of Asking Bids for use in 'strong' sequences.  The system I teach is loosely based on Eric Jannerstern's description of Super-Precision, but heavily modified from that. 
|
