|cp|red|at|^*bOliverC:^*n|cp||at|  I mentioned the website. Besides holding details of the full system in exhaustive detail, the site also boasts a discussion forum where you can raise problems you've encountered using the system, suggest changes, or just discuss the system with others using it. 

You can register for the Forum at ^*h http://ocp.pigpen.org.uk/smf/index.php ^*n, but please use your BBO UserID and genuine Email Address to do so. 

I get a lot of spurious registrations, so I tend to delete ones I don't recognise. The website is the definitive description of the current state of the system. Any changes to the system are reflected THERE before any changes are made to the downloadable documents or the Full Disclosure Convention Cards (see below).

Those "others" using the system generally form a Team called the Precision BILlies. Besides being a competitive Team in various different combinations for different competitions, we also try to run a mentoring scheme whereby those of us who are more experienced with the system help those still learning it.

If you are seriously interested in learning and using the system, you will not be alone!!  We try to run the mentoring groups broadly on time-zone lines to match Mentors and "Mentees" in similar time zones so that they are like to be on BBO at similar times. 

If you are interested, register on the Precision Site and send me an email to express an interest in the scheme and we'll try to organise things.

The activities, practices, tutorials etc are publicised on the website and if you are starting to learn the system, please let us know so that we can include you in the mentoring scheme if you want to take advantage of it. 

In addition to the scheduled practices you will often find members of the Team playing on BBO, and kibitzing them will add to your understanding of the system. 
